[{"category":"section","location":"#Chebyshaw","page":"Home","text":"Documentation for Chebyshaw.\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.AbstractChebyshevSeries-Tuple{T} where T","page":"Home","text":"(f::AbstractChebyshevSeries{T,1})(x::T) where T -> T\n\nSimpler callable constructor for evaluating a one-dimensional Chebyshev series f at a point x, where x is of type T.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.AbstractChebyshevSeries"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.AbstractChebyshevSeries-Union{Tuple{AbstractVector{T}}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"(f::AbstractChebyshevSeries{T,N})(x::AbstractVector{T}) where {T,N} -> T\n\nSimpler callable constructor for evaluating a Chebyshev series f at a point x, where x is of any subtype of an AbstractVector{T}.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.AbstractChebyshevSeries"},{"category":"type","location":"#Chebyshaw.ChebyshevCluster","page":"Home","text":"ChebyshevCluster{T, N, M}\n\nA collection of M equidimensional ChebyshevSeries objects.\n\nFields\n\nseries::NTuple{M,ChebyshevSeries{T,N}}: N-dimensional Chebyshev series\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.ChebyshevCluster"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.ChebyshevCluster-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{ChebyshevSeries{T, N}, Vararg{ChebyshevSeries{T, N}}}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"ChebyshevCluster(f::ChebyshevSeries{T,N}...) where {T,N} -> ChebyshevCluster{T,N,M}\n\nSimpler constructor for a Chebyshev cluster.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.ChebyshevCluster"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.ChebyshevCluster-Union{Tuple{StaticArraysCore.SVector{N, T}}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"(h::ChebyshevCluster{T,N})(x::SVector{N,T}) where {T,N} -> T\n\nEvaluates the Chebyshev cluster h at a point x.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.ChebyshevCluster"},{"category":"type","location":"#Chebyshaw.ChebyshevSeries","page":"Home","text":"ChebyshevSeries{T,N}\n\nThe Chebyshev series approximation of a N-dimensional function defined in a bounded domain.\n\nFields\n\ncoefs::Array{T,N}: coefficients\nlb::SVector{N,T}: domain lower bound\nub::SVector{N,T}: domain upper bound\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.ChebyshevSeries"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.ChebyshevSeries-Union{Tuple{StaticArraysCore.SVector{N, T}}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"(f::ChebyshevSeries{T,N})(x::SVector{N,T}) where {T,N} -> T\n\nEvaluates the Chebyshev series f at a point x.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.ChebyshevSeries"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.ChebyshevSeries-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Array{T, 0}, StaticArraysCore.SVector{0, T}, StaticArraysCore.SVector{0, T}}} where T","page":"Home","text":"ChebyshevSeries(coefs::Array{T,0}, lb::SVector{0,T}, ub::SVector{0,T}) where T -> T\n\nA zero-dimensional Chebyshev series is just the coefficient.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.ChebyshevSeries"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.ChebyshevSeries-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Vector{T}, T, T}} where T","page":"Home","text":"ChebyshevSeries(coefs::Array{T,1}, lb::T, ub::T) where T -> ChebyshevSeries{T,1}\n\nSimpler constructor for one-dimensional Chebyshev series.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.ChebyshevSeries"},{"category":"type","location":"#Chebyshaw.TransformedChebyshevSeries","page":"Home","text":"TransformedChebyshevSeries{T,N}\n\nThe transformation of a Chebyshev series in the domain u to the domain x.\n\nFields\n\nseries::ChebyshevSeries{T,N}: series in the domain u\nu::F: transformation function u(x)\n∇u::G: transformation function gradient u(x)\nHu::H: transformation function hessian mathrmHu(x)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.TransformedChebyshevSeries"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.TransformedChebyshevSeries-Union{Tuple{ChebyshevSeries{T, N}}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"TransformedChebyshevSeries(\n    series::ChebyshevSeries{T,N}\n) where {T,N} -> TransformedChebyshevSeries{T,N}\n\nIdentically transformed Chebyshev series.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.TransformedChebyshevSeries"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.TransformedChebyshevSeries-Union{Tuple{StaticArraysCore.SVector{N, T}}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"(f::ChebyshevSeries{T,N})(x::SVector{N,T}) where {T,N} -> T\n\nEvaluates the transformed Chebyshev series g at a point x, which is equivalent to evaluating g.series at the point g.u(x).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.TransformedChebyshevSeries"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.clenshaw-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{Array{T, N}, StaticArraysCore.SVector{N, T}}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"clenshaw(a::Array{T,N}, x::SVector{N,T}) where {T,N} -> T\n\nImplements the Clenshaw algorithm to evaluate the N-th dimensional Chebyshev series with coefficients a at a normalized point x in -1 1^N.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.clenshaw"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.clenshaw-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{Array{T, N}, T}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"clenshaw(a::Array{T,N}, x::T) where {T,N} -> Array{T,N-1}\n\nImplements the Clenshaw algorithm to evaluate the N-th dimensional Chebyshev series with coefficients a at a normalized value x of its N-th dimension.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.clenshaw"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.contains-Union{Tuple{M}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{ChebyshevCluster{T, N, M}, StaticArraysCore.SVector{N, T}}} where {T, N, M}","page":"Home","text":"contains(h::ChebyshevCluster{T,N,M}, x::SVector{N,T}) where {T,N,M} -> Int\n\nFinds the index of the series in the cluster h where the point x is located. Returns 0 if x is not in h.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.contains"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.contains-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{ChebyshevSeries{T, N}, StaticArraysCore.SVector{N, T}}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"contains(f::ChebyshevSeries{T,N}, x::SVector{N,T}) where {T,N} -> Bool\n\nChecks if the point x is in the domain of f.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.contains"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.contains-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{ChebyshevSeries{T, N}, T}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"function contains(f::ChebyshevSeries{T,N}, x::T; dim::Int=N) where {T,N} -> Bool\n\nChecks if the point x is in the domain of the dimension dim of f.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.contains"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.contains-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TransformedChebyshevSeries{T, N}, StaticArraysCore.SVector{N, T}}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"contains(g::TransformedChebyshevSeries{T,N}, x::SVector{N,T}) where {T,N} -> Bool\n\nChecks if the point x is in the domain of g, which is equivalent to checking if the point g.u(x) is in the domain of g.series.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.contains"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.domain-Union{Tuple{ChebyshevSeries{T, N}}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"domain(f::ChebyshevSeries{T,N}) where {T,N} -> String\n\nDomain of the Chebyshev series given as the cartesian product of closed intervals along each dimension. The lower and upper bounds of the intervals are rounded to three digits of decimal precision.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.domain"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.gradient-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{Chebyshaw.AbstractChebyshevSeries{T, N}, AbstractVector{T}}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"gradient(\n    f::AbstractChebyshevSeries{T,N}, x::AbstractVector{T}\n) where {T,N} -> T, SVector{N,T}\n\nSimpler function for evaluating a Chebyshev series f and its gradient at a point x, where x is of any subtype of an AbstractVector{T}.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.gradient"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.gradient-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{ChebyshevCluster{T, N}, StaticArraysCore.SVector{N, T}}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"gradient(h::ChebyshevCluster{T,N}, x::SVector{N,T}) where {T,N} -> T, SVector{N,T}\n\nEvaluates the Chebyshev cluster h and its gradient at a point x.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.gradient"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.gradient-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{ChebyshevSeries{T, N}, StaticArraysCore.SVector{N, T}}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"gradient(f::ChebyshevSeries{T,N}, x::SVector{N,T}) where {T,N} -> T, SVector{N,T}\n\nEvaluates the Chebyshev series f and its gradient at a point x.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.gradient"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.gradient-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TransformedChebyshevSeries{T, N}, StaticArraysCore.SVector{N, T}}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"gradient(\n    g::TransformedChebyshevSeries{T, N}, x::SVector{N, T}\n) where {T, N} -> T, SVector{N, T}\n\nEvaluates the transformed Chebyshev series g and its gradient at a point x.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.gradient"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.gradient-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Chebyshaw.AbstractChebyshevSeries{T, 1}, T}} where T","page":"Home","text":"gradient(f::AbstractChebyshevSeries{T,1}, x::T) where T -> T, T\n\nSimpler function for evaluating a one-dimensional Chebyshev series f and its gradient at a point x, where x is of type T.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.gradient"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.gradient_clenshaw-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{Array{T, N}, StaticArraysCore.SVector{N, T}}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"gradient_clenshaw(a::Array{T,N}, x::SVector{N,T}) where {T,N} -> T, SVector{N,T}\n\nImplements the Clenshaw algorithm to evaluate the N-th dimensional Chebyshev series with coefficients a and its gradient at a normalized point x in -1 1^N.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.gradient_clenshaw"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.gradient_clenshaw-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{Array{T, N}, T}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"gradient_clenshaw(a::Array{T,N}, x::T) where {T,N} -> Array{T,N-1}, Array{T,N-1}\n\nImplements the Clenshaw algorithm to evaluate the N-th dimensional Chebyshev series with coefficients a and its gradient at a normalized value x of its N-th dimension.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.gradient_clenshaw"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.hessian-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{Chebyshaw.AbstractChebyshevSeries{T, N}, AbstractVector{T}}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"hessian(\n    f::AbstractChebyshevSeries{T,N}, x::AbstractVector{T}\n) where {T,N} -> T, SVector{N,T}, SMatrix{N,N,T}\n\nSimpler function for evaluating a Chebyshev series f, its gradient and hessian at a point x, where x is of any subtype of an AbstractVector{T}.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.hessian"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.hessian-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{ChebyshevCluster{T, N}, StaticArraysCore.SVector{N, T}}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"hessian(\n    h::ChebyshevCluster{T,N}, x::SVector{N,T}\n) where {T,N} -> T, SVector{N,T}, SMatrix{N,N,T}\n\nEvaluates the Chebyshev cluster h, its gradient and hessian at a point x.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.hessian"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.hessian-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{ChebyshevSeries{T, N}, StaticArraysCore.SVector{N, T}}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"hessian(\n    f::ChebyshevSeries{T,N}, x::SVector{N,T}\n) where {T,N} -> T, SVector{N,T}, SMatrix{N,N,T}\n\nEvaluates the Chebyshev series f, its gradient and hessian at a point x.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.hessian"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.hessian-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{TransformedChebyshevSeries{T, N}, StaticArraysCore.SVector{N, T}}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"hessian(\n    g::TransformedChebyshevSeries{T,N}, x::SVector{N,T}\n) where {T,N} -> T, SVector{N,T}, SMatrix{N,N,T}\n\nEvaluates the transformed Chebyshev series g, its gradient and hessian at a point x.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.hessian"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.hessian-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Chebyshaw.AbstractChebyshevSeries{T, 1}, T}} where T","page":"Home","text":"hessian(f::AbstractChebyshevSeries{T,1}, x::T) where T -> T, T, T\n\nSimpler function for evaluating a one-dimensional Chebyshev series f, its gradient and hessian at a point x, where x is of type T.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.hessian"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.hessian_clenshaw-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{Array{T, N}, StaticArraysCore.SVector{N, T}}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"hessian_clenshaw(\n    a::Array{T,N}, x::SVector{N,T}\n) where {T,N} -> T, SVector{N,T}, SMatrix{N,N,T}\n\nImplements the Clenshaw algorithm to evaluate the N-th dimensional Chebyshev series with coefficients a, its gradient and hessian at a normalized point x in -1 1^N.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.hessian_clenshaw"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.hessian_clenshaw-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{Array{T, N}, T}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"hessian_clenshaw(\n    a::Array{T,N}, x::T\n) where {T,N} -> Array{T,N-1}, Array{T,N-1}, Array{T,N-1}\n\nImplements the Clenshaw algorithm to evaluate the N-th dimensional Chebyshev series with coefficients a, its gradient and hessian at a normalized value x of its N-th dimension.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.hessian_clenshaw"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.normalize-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{ChebyshevSeries{T, N}, StaticArraysCore.SVector{N, T}}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"normalize(f::ChebyshevSeries{T,N}, x::SVector{N,T}) where {T,N} -> SVector{N,T}\n\nConverts a point x to its normalized coordinates in -1 1^N.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.normalize"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.normalize-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{ChebyshevSeries{T, N}, T}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"normalize(f::ChebyshevSeries{T,N}, x::T; dim::Int=N) where {T,N} -> T\n\nConverts a point x in the dimension dim of f to its normalized coordinates in -1 1\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.normalize"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.order-Union{Tuple{ChebyshevSeries{T, 1}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"Home","text":"order(f::ChebyshevSeries{T,1}) where T -> Int\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.order"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.order-Union{Tuple{ChebyshevSeries{T, N}}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"order(f::ChebyshevSeries{T,N}) where {T,N} -> NTuple{N,Int}\n\nChebyshev series order, which is equal to the number of coefficients along each dimension minus one.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.order"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.reduce-Union{Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{ChebyshevSeries{T, N}, T}} where {T, N}","page":"Home","text":"reduce(f::ChebyshevSeries{T,N}, x::T; dim::Int=N) where {T,N} -> ChebyshevSeries{T,N-1}\n\nEvalautes a N-dimensional Chebyshev series at a value of x of its dimension dim, thus reducing the series dimension to N-1.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.reduce"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.symmatrix-Union{Tuple{K}, Tuple{N}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{StaticArraysCore.SVector{K, T}, Val{N}}} where {T, N, K}","page":"Home","text":"symmatrix(u::SVector{K,T}, ::Val{N}) where {T,N,K} -> SMatrix{N,N,T}\n\nConverts a vector of K values representing the upper triangular matrix of order N, stored in column-major order, into a symmetric matrix of order N. It's necessary that K = N*(N+1)÷2.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.symmatrix"},{"category":"method","location":"#Chebyshaw.validate_transformation-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Type{T}, Int64, Any, Any, Any}} where T","page":"Home","text":"validate_transformation(::Type{T}, N::Int, u, ∇u, Hu) where T\n\nValidates the input and return types of u, ∇u and Hu.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Chebyshaw.validate_transformation"}]
